libmdr (0.8.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fixed double-free
  * Retry writes after EINTR, don't abort on EAGAIN, just return and retry
    later
  * Fixed error reporting after SSL_accept error
  * Don't abort connection once the write BIO is empty
  * Fix possible connection stall if we receive multiple TLS records at once
  * Fixed resource leak on shutdown
  * Fixed possible fd corruption (closing the wrong fd; seemingly only on BSD)
  * Fix tlsev_close() invocation on OpenBSD
  * idxheap_top() should really be a _peek(0) rather than remove. So do that,
    then add a new idxheap_pop() that does remove the top entry. More
    intuitive like that.
  * Explicitly handle null peer_cert in pack_bein(); not a bug with
    OpenSSL/LibreSSL, but this is not documented behavior so err on the
    side of caution
  * Fix leak in strarray_add when realloc fails
  * manpages & doc

 -- Pascal Lalonde <plalonde@overnet.ca>  Sat, 16 May 2026 22:25:27 -0400

libmdr (0.8.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Don't let decoding be fooled by a massive array size for strings/mdrs that
    would never be able to fit in a message of a given size. This reduces the
    burden on users when allocating an array; if they bound their message
    sizes, the allocated array will also be bounded.
  * Fix possible stall in client session if multiple SSL records are read
    from the socket in one call. SSL_read() will read at most 1 processed
    record so we have to loop on SSL_read() to make sure to drain our
    BIO_s_mem.
  * Fix rcvlowat in situations where we could clamp the value to 2^14
  * Tweak README
  * eliminate unaligned reads/writes
  * Remove sigaction from 'stat' command. First off it was not properly
    uninitialized and generally not useful for a short interactive command.
  * Fix dirent underflow
  * Fix possible out of bounds reads for string/mdr arrays
  * Fix another integer overflow which could allow out-of-bounds array access
  * Make sure to enable host validation during SSL verification

 -- Pascal Lalonde <plalonde@overnet.ca>  Thu, 14 May 2026 22:40:46 -0400

libmdr (0.8.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix a remote crash when sending zero-byte strings to mdrd
  * Make sure we actually reject sessions with certs over the allowed limit
  * Fix null deref when we don't define allowed domains in the config
  * Fix non-blocking behavior on the control socket
  * Fix stack overflow in flatconf.y
  * Fix drop_privileges invocation where uid/gid were swapped
  * Though unlikely, don't abort on BIO_get_mem_data() failures (BIO_mem)
  * Fix EINTR condition in sendmsg()

